movies.title: Frat Party
movies.plot: Duffy, a former campus king of one-night stands and kinky threesomes, has one final blowout on the night before his wedding. Before making it to the altar, he will have to survive Asian masseuses, horny ex-girlfriends, strip beer-pong, S&M booby traps, and the temptations of adult film superstar.

biography.bio: Randy Wayne was born on August 7, 1981 in Moore, Oklahoma, USA as Randy Wayne Frederick. He is an actor and producer, known for Honey 2 (2011), Hellraiser: Judgment (2017) and The Dukes of Hazzard: The Beginning (2007).
biography.name: Randy Wayne

biography.bio: Caroline D'Amore was born on June 9, 1984 in Los Angeles, California, USA. She is an actress, known for Sorority Row (2009), Frat Party (2009) and Pizza with Bullets (2015). She has been married to Bobby Alt since August 5, 2012. They have one child.
biography.name: Caroline D'Amore

biography.bio: Jareb Dauplaise is from a small town where he was raised with his two brothers Adam and Daniel Dauplaise by his mother Myla Bunner-Eckert and step-father Rusty Eckert. Jareb always wanted to be an actor but wasn't sure how to do it. With help from his family including his grandma Patricia Lytton and mostly God he finished school and moved to Hollywood by himself. After a year, he was lucky enough to book an episode of Entourage which helped him get noticed.
biography.name: Jareb Dauplaise

biography.bio: Lauren Courtney Mayhew was born on 27 November 1985 in Tampa, Florida to David Mayhew, an orthopaedic surgeon and Sharon Mayhew, a nurse. She has a sister named Briana, who was born in 1988. Lauren started in acting at the age of 9 when she was a finalist in the national Wilhemnia contest. A judge, Marilyn Zitner, who was a manager in New York, signed her. She booked the role of Marah Lewis on Guiding Light and went on to guest star on numerous TV shows. Lauren took a break and signed with Sony records to be part of the group PYT, which went on to release an album and tour with Destiny's Child, NYSC, and Brittany Spears. Lauren preformed at the preshow for the Super Bowl in 2001, and has been featured in numerous magazines with PYT. Last year she started back in acting and recently booked a reoccurring role on American Dreams. She is continuing with her song writing and producing.
biography.name: Lauren C. Mayhew

biography.bio: Dan Levy's mother placed him in a comedy class at the age of nine. Enrolled at Emerson College in Boston, Dan jump-started his career as a stand-up comedian while maintaining his full-time student status. By the end of his freshman year, Dan performed regularly at The Comedy Connection, Nick's Comedy Stop, and The Comedy Studio. He spent that summer interning for "The Daily Show with Jon Stewart" and performing at various New York City venues, such as The Comic Strip Live. His comedy career took off when he was chosen to compete for the title of "Funniest College Comedian in America" at the 2001 Aspen U.S. Comedy Arts Festival. Dan won the title and signed a deal with the All-True Network in New York City, where he wrote and created the comedic reality show "The Dan Levy Show."
biography.name: Dan Levy
